    {
      "_id": "G7I9h7u2sZHrBCCC",
      "name": "Weeping Pox",
      "type": "feat",
      "system": {
        "source": {
          "custom": "",
          "book": "GHMG",
          "page": "273",
          "license": ""
        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A humanoid that comes within 5 feet of the putrid giant or anything it has recently held must succeed on a [[/save ability=constitution dc=15]] saving throw or contract @disease[The Weeping Pox|GH|Weeping Pox]. If a humanoid succeeds on the saving throw, it's immune to the disease for 24 hours. A humanoid infected with the disease must repeat the saving throw every 24 hours, increasing its &amp;Reference[condition=exhaustion] level by one on a failure. This &amp;Reference[condition=exhaustion] can't be reduced until the disease is cured. The disease can be cured only with magic.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Until the first level of &amp;Reference[condition=exhaustion] sets in, however, the humanoid has sharpened senses and a sense of wellbeing. Whenever this humanoid makes an ability check or saving throw against anything other than the disease, they can roll a [[/r d4]] and add the number rolled to the ability check or saving throw. A slight fever and overexcitement are the only signs this condition comes from @disease[The Weeping Pox|GH|Weeping Pox].</p></div>",
